Variable is a property that can take up any value

Height = 150cm, Gender=Male ..etc are variables 

Different Types Of Variables:

1. Quantitative Variables:

   2 types:  
   1. Discrete Quantitative variables:  Whole number not fraction. A took  4 chocolates ( not 4.5)
   2. Continuous Quantitative variables:
   A is eating 20.9 gms of protein today 

Qualitative or categorical Variables:
Gender: Male or Female 
Colors: Red, Green Blue 

All these are not numerical variables, these are categorical variables. These are also called Qualitative values 

